class Main {
  static {
    System.loadLibrary("libraryname");
  }
  
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    test();
  }
  
  private static native void test();
}

content.text: The native keyword declares a method as belonging to an external compiled library which is native to the operating system.
content.html: The native keyword declares a method as belonging to an external compiled library which is native to the operating system.

content.text: In order to use native methods, an external library must be loaded from a .dll , .so or similar kind of file. The compiled code in the external file should be written to support the Java Native Interface.
